sources.title: Green Eyes
sources.description: A charming Chesterfield mystery starring 1930s/40s hero Charles Starrett. The owner of a large mansion in the country throws a costume party for some of his friends. However, the party turns sour when he is found stabbed to death in a closet. The police and a guest try to discover who committed the murder. Encoded for IPOD from a VHS master.

sources.title: Green Eyes
sources.description: The murder of a rich industrialist at a costume party throws suspicion on sundry guests including his grand-daughter, a mystery writer, and a business associate from Mexico. Find out more about this movie on its IMDB page .

sources.title: Green Eyes (1934) MYSTERY
sources.description:
Stars: Shirley Grey, Charles Starrett, Claude Gillingwater 
Director: Richard Thorpe

The owner of a large mansion in the country throws a costume party for some of his friends. However, the party turns sour when he is found stabbed to death in a closet!
